reviews.text: We had a wonderful afternoon at the Southern Vermont Arts Center. Our family enjoyed being able to get up close to the sculptures around the property and the main photography exhibit was stunningly beautiful and complex. Instamax cameras were given out to the kids so that the could experience photography. A beautiful, short trail leads out from a second building housing galleries that display the work of local artists.
Beautiful grounds; very interesting sculptures dot the landscape. Free admission.
Good place to enjoy a lot of VT art. Multiple buildings and interesting outdoor art.
Great location, really beautiful views. Visited the location for the great 2016 solarfest. The Asian resturant on site has great food.
The drive to the art center is lined with beautiful sculptures, and the buildings have an interesting history.
The Fly fishing history is amazing. Looks small from the outside but there is a ton to see on the inside.
Great for fishing, but they do not teach you how to fly. ;)
They have Bing Crosby's hat, fishing pole, and a number of the fly's he made! Oh, and a lot of items from past presidents and other notable historic persons.
This is a must stop if you are in Vermont. Great exhibits.
Very informative, learned more than I expected. Could stand to have some soft background music.
Very good coming back for Oklahoma
Great shows and very kind volunteers
Great venue for plays, concerts and much more
1st time visit.  Easy to find. Nice theater.  Saw "Pride & Prejudice" this afternoon.  Great cast!!  Particular kudos to Lydia, Elizabeth & Mary😊
First-class theater company. Outstanding, professional performances and stories. Never disappointing, always uplifting and thought provoking.
First time in Vermont and I have to say, what a beautiful place! Vermont is beautiful. First time was a success

This inn is actually so much more than that. There are several smaller cottages converted into rooms and a very large home which can be rented out for large groups. 

Breakfast is great, and the views are incredible!
Terrific staff, very comfortable room, breakfast extraordinaire!  Plus: location, location, location.  Had a wonderful time; thanks very much!---Danny Domoff

The staff here was extremely hospitable; everyone we met really went above and beyond. The accommodations were clean and well-appointed. The bed in room 16 was a little high and might not be the best option for elderly visitors. The grounds were well kept and beautifully relaxing. The breakfast was fresh and delicious, we only wish we could have been able to get lunch and or dinner there too.

Was a great experience. Love the old fashion inn and the views around the property. Staff are very friendly, booking was easy, and got a great rate. Not even a 10 minute drive to downtown which was perfect. Would stay again.
Super high quality, fresh fish. Amazingly friendly, professional and masterful proprietors. Diamond in the rough.
Very nice owners. Welcoming to travelers and locals alike. They try to make everything delicious. Small cafe, small tables. Nice place to meet a friend or go on a date.
Great sushi! Even better owners =)
Always good. We took out this time, but it's a cozy little place to eat in. Also, you can BYOB!
Consistently delicious (especially the Spicy Shrimp Dragon!), always freshly created and I love the atmosphere!

This is the best bagel place ever!! I went with my super picky 7 year old and I knew it was going to be a problem getting him something he'll be happy with. I was dying to have a breakfast jalapeno bagel which I did. Anyway, the ladies were so incredibly understanding, not annoyed at all at the fact that my son like nothing but chicken. They had tons of suggestions and patience.  Always with a huge smile and and sincerity.  Love the service and my breakfast bagel! Thank you!!
Reallly like this place. Healthy options. Gluten free items too. They have stevia for your coffee instead of those chemical options other coffee places have. Their Broth Bowl is amazing.
Great bagel and cream cheese. My first time but won't be my last.

Well designed and appointed room with very comfortable bed & luxurious bathroom.  Excellent food, both in the dining room as well as room service. Fitness center very clean & adequately equipped (including Peloton).
Good bagles made daily.  My go to is a Jalapeno cheddar bagle with ham egg and cheese.

I gotta say, this pains me to write this review,  I’ve beem coming up to This area since I was a kid and always wanted to try Garlic Johns. Unfortunately this will be my one and only time here. While my garlic and oil pasta with anchovies was pretty good the service was abysmal
There were only 3 of us eating main course that was just pasta and the food took over one and a half hours to come out. It took 1 hour to get the salad lol(which was good also) 
Additionally it was impossible to get any of the wait staffs attention; I felt like a part of a ground flight crew the amount of times I was waving my arms. 

Can I get a refill of water
I ordered a coke when I first sat down and I never got it
Can you check with the kitchen to see if the foods done.

All this and the restaurant was not even full at all, overall food was decent but I’d say take it to go..
Very good menu, super service, interesting decor well priced. Casual dining experience.
Great atmosphere and very good food. Enjoyed my egg-plant dinner. The only negative is there are steps to get in and my knees are not great. I would return to this restaurant for dinner again.

Fantastic! The Vodka sauce was superb! The Bread to die for! One suggestion would be to serve garlic oil with the bread, not just the oil. We appreciated our waitress bringing us garlic for the oil though. Our waitress had only been at your restaurant for a couple of weeks. Keep her! She was great! What she didn't know, she found out and she was there for our group of 5 whenever we needed her but didn't hover. We'll be back!
Good - food, drinks, service, atmosphere,  and prices.

Everything our party ordered was outstanding: halibut, chicken breast, duck, steak. Each was well-prepared, well-seasoned, and accompanied by excellent and appropriate side dishes. The European-style salad starter was as delicious as promised, and the dessert strawberry special with a zabione sauce was indeed special. Add to this a beautiful interior ambiance and helpful service. This restaurant does close for a break during Vermont's "mud season" but is a place not to be missed in summer and winter.

Wow. We just had dinner for the first time and it was excellent! We came in on a mid-week night in the middle of a snow storm and the place was half full, we sat on the side that was not full (empty) next to Dennis the penguin. It was a little awkward with us being the only ones on that side of the dining room, there were lots of chickens everywhere, and the background elevator music was really something but once we got used to it man that was a great meal. Our hostess/waitress was super welcoming, totally on top of the experience, and the service was excellent. The food start to finish was excellent too. The escargot was amazing, so garlicky, and perfectly cooked. The schnitzel was very light and tender, sirloin was cooked dead on perfect med rare and a very nice cut, and both the fries and spatzle where very tasty. Oh, best side/starter salad ever. Can't wait to go back!
Phenomenal food. Excellent service. Nice ambiance.
Excellent food! Best duck I've ever had, time and time again. It's not cheap but well worth the money. Always excellent...
Tammy was great.  My wife loved the Dover sole. Funny that wasn't on any of the menus around Mt. Snow.

Hidden gem. 

Excellent donuts. Possibly some of the best donuts. My kids agree.  One dozen for a little less than 10 dollars. CASH ONLY.

Sourdough is excellent. 
Apple crisp is excellent. 

By 1 o'clock many selections are sold out. 

Coffee however is interestingly non-potable. But good for dunking donuts. They should invest a little into decent beans to match the quality of donuts. 

Service is friendly and helpful. 

Store front is nondescript. Inside is small, 70s and beyond (meaning way before) style furnishings. Blast from the past.
My kids insist on Mrs. Murphys Donuts because "they are way better than Dunkin, Dad".  Recommend the granulated jelly donut if you need a sugar boost.
Great place, come here Everytime we are in Manchester village.
The best donuts in the world!
Always fresh and good!

Dependably good food with a very friendly staff and reasonable prices.Their nightly specials are very good and reasonably priced. I have been going their since the day they opened in the 60's, it has changed a lot with new ownership but they have retained the great hamburgers John and Jim offered so long ago. Our go to "family" restaurant.

This is probably the best restaurant I've ever eaten at. It was truly excellent. Delicious house specialties, they even custom make a selection of unique house sauces and beverages! A lovely staff completes this little bit of heaven on earth.
Our dinner was excellent. We had the veggie melt and shrimp scampi. Service was friendly and timely, quaint country atmosphere and didn't have to wait long for seating on a Friday night.

Excellent food and service very friendly staff. Usually a packed house but definitely worth the wait. The menu has so many great dishes but my all time favorite is the Seafood Steam Pot. A must have for any seafood lover.

Salads are good.  Rib eye.. not great. Overall, We had a fine meal and we'd be back if it weren't for our amazingly, incredibly, jaw droppingly rude waitress.  I was not surprised to see a common thread of complaints on Trip Advisor and many complaints about the rude hostess/manager/ owner on google.  The more polite we were, the angrier she became.  bizarre evening to say the least.

This is hands down one of the best places I have ever gotten amazing food from. I would always reccomend going here if you get the chance. Their catering service is likely top-notch as well, as all the employees and owners are extraordinarily nice and skilled people.
One of my favorite lunch spots..great soups, sandwiches, hot foods. Have also used their catering services. Best cheesesteaks in the area too
Love this place my favorite everything is great the owner and staff are great
Amazing food! Just wish you guys were open Sunday
Only place I know that has good scrapple sandwiches!!!
